This paper deals with the task of object class annotation, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The approach proposed in the paper involves mapping raw input strings to entities in an ontology, which is a technique commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also leverages inter-annotator co-occurrences and biases, which are techniques used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.CL, followed by cs.IR, cs.LG, and cs.AI.
